*** AquaCrop
- Simulates daily biomass production and final crop yield
- Biomass production is a function of transpiration
- "...a crop grows by developing a canopy and accumulating biomass in daily time
  steps. Crop phenology simulated in terms of growing degree days that
  accumulate over the season."
- The effect of various stresses (e.g. temperature, water availability) are
  simulated using coefficients.
- Foliage development is simulated in terms of green canopy cover rather than
  leaf area index; a feature which differenatiates the model from many other
  crop models. Canopy cover varies between zero, before emergence, to a maximum
  value defined by the parameter CCx, which has a maximum value of 100%. 
