run.py -> Configuration, DeterministicRunner -> WaterBalanceModel
WaterBalanceModel contains four modules represented by objects of the classes:
1. Meteo
2. Groundwater
3. CanalSupply
4. LandSurface
The first three of these are relatively straightforward. Objects of class
LandSurface contain a list of objects inheriting from the LandCover class. This
is an implementation of the tiled approach for representing subgrid
heterogeneity, which is common in land surface modelling and other types of
gridded hydrological model. The standard version of AquaCrop-Python only
considers cropland. This is represented by an object of class AquaCropLandCover,
which implements the AquaCrop model routines. However, the possibility of
including additional land cover types (e.g. forest, grassland) opens up the
possibility of extending the standard implementation to represent the entire
land surface in the manner of a land surface or hydrological model. To
facilitate this, the LandSurface class includes methods to aggregate variables
from multiple LandCover objects. 


